      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DIVINE VICKY (1) consistent mare who looks set to peak at her third run back today. Strong through the line with the 60.5kg when a slashing fourth over this trip at Wyong. Adept in all conditions and can run a touch closer from the good gate. LIGHT INFANTRY (4) underrated gelding who demolished a solid field first-up over 1200m at Parkes in C2 grade. Raced without luck in Highway class last prep and can go on with it this time in. MAGNOLIA JEWEL (8) sharp improver on the quick back-up when she ploughed through the heavy conditions to score a well-deserved victory over 1106m at Port Macquarie. Well placed with the claim and comes here deep into the campaign. PRINZERRO (2) winkers go on for this with the key jockey change. Came back a level second-up when he faded in the straight to finish seventh over 1200m at Newcastle after showing good early speed. Can find form from the better gate.",
